{"word":"ἰάομαι","slug":"ἰάομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἰάομαι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <a href='S:vide'>v.</a> infr. [<el>ῑᾱ</el> <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>,; later also <el>ι]</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to heal, cure</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:— <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>ἀδικίαν ἰᾶσθαι</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>: proverb., <el>μὴ τῶι κακῶι τὸ κακὸν ἰῶ</el>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> do not make bad worse, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>the aor1 <el>ἰάθην [ᾱ]</el> is always <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a>, <i>to be healed, to recover</i>, <b><a href='S:Andocides'>Andoc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>; so <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>ἴᾱμαι</el> <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}